         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#chaniotis2024">
            <p><note>a</note>: To the first mother Aphrodite and the People, Imperator Caesar Nerva Trajanus Augustus restored (this) from the will of Adrastos Grypos, son of Pereitas, 
               through Kallikrates Grypos, son of Pereitas, priest, supervisor of the work.</p>
            <p><note>b</note>: The People prepared and restored the statues of "the Cyclops", thrown down, shattered and made useless by an earthquake, at their own expense.</p>
         </div>
         
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#iaph2007">
            <p><note>a</note>: For the first mother Aphrodite and the People. Imperator Caesar Nerva Trajanus Augustus restored (this) from the will of Adrastos son of Pereitas ? Grypos, 
               through Kallikrates son of Pereitas Grypos, priest, supervisor of the work.</p>
            <p><note>b</note>: The People prepared and restored the statues of the Cyclops, thrown down, shattered and made useless by an earthquake, at its own expense.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" source="#jmr1982">
            <p><note>a</note>: To the first mother Aphrodite and the Demos. Imperator Caesar Nerva Trajanus Augustus, Germanicus, Dacicus, restored (this) with the legacy from 
               Adrastos Grypus son of Pereitas, 
               through Callicrates Grypus son of Pereitas, priest, superintendent of the work.</p>
         </div>
         
